<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/158: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Riddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-11T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 11,
                                        1922—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:16
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>52. Department’s 34, August 7, 4 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs today
                            informed me that in view of Western Company’s renunciation, <pb facs="0656" n="536" xml:id="pg_536"/> the Argentine Government does
                            not consider that contract constitutes an obstacle to granting equal
                            privileges to an American company and he promised me early written note
                            in confirmation. …</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Riddle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>